This part mostly lg, but I do not like how we handle instance types and cluster specifications separately here. Consider merging the block at L58 with this block, using one of the following

```
# Option 1 -- use functions

def resolve_system_requirements_input(instance_type=None, cluster_specification=None):
    system_requirements = {}
    # Code
    return system_requirements

--//--

run_input["systemRequirements"] = resolve_system_requirements_input(instance_type=kwargs.get("instance_type"), cluster_specification=kwargs.get("merged_cluster_spec"))
```

or

```
# Option 2 -- use classes

class SystemRequirementsDict(object):
    def __init__(self, ...): ...
    @classmethod
    def from_instance_type(cls, instance_type=None):
        return cls(...)
    @classmethod
    def from_cluster_specification(cls, cluster_specification=None):
        return cls(...)

    def __add__(self, srd):
        """Add only, raise on collisions"""
        if not isinstance(srd, SystemRequirementsDict): raise
        # Code
        return SystemRequirementsDict(...)

    def add_override(self, srd)
        # Code
        return SRD(...)

    def as_dict(self): ...
--//--

run_input["systemRequirements"] = (SystemRequirementsDict.from_instance_type(...) + SRD.from_cluster_specification(...)).as_dict()
```

