Yes, we need to wrap the Action Button with the stopPropagationWrapper. 

Without it, if we click an ActionButton, it will also pass the click event up to the parent, where it will trigger the collapsible.

```
     <ActionButton
                          className={hiddenButtonStyle}
                          icon={removeIcon}
                          title={'Apply stash entry (prop wrapper)'}
                          onClick={props.stopPropagationWrapper(() => {
                            gitStashApply(entry.index);
                          })}
                        />
```


With it, if we click an ActionButton, we will not trigger the parent collapsible.

```
  <ActionButton
                          className={hiddenButtonStyle}
                          icon={removeIcon}
                          title={'Apply stash entry (no prop wrapper)'}
                          onClick={() => {
                            gitStashApply(entry.index);
                          }}
                        />
```


