https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/master/sdk/nodejs/stackReference.ts#L19-L123

A stack reference is currently constructed using the name of the referenced stack. The implementation calls `GetStackOutputs` on the backend interface, which ends up calling `/export` and finding the stack's outputs from the state file. After the stack reference is created, the user calls `getOutput` to get specific outputs.

```
// Create a reference to stack "foo". The reference will have all of foo's outputs.
var foo = new StackReference("foo");

// Use specific outputs from "foo".
foo.getOutput("a").apply(a => console.log(a));
```

In order to have information about output usage, we would need to know the outputs the user needed at the point of `new StackReference`. @ekrengel can you expand on what in https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/issues/2309 seems like it could use this info?

