There are 3 conditions:

```py
# Condition 1: managedByTenants missing
{

}

# Condition 2: managedByTenants is null
{
    "managedByTenants": null
}

# Condition 3: managedByTenants is empty list []
{
    "managedByTenants": []
}
```

This statement doesn't take condition 2 `"managedByTenants": null` into consideration. If ARM returns `"managedByTenants": null`, Azure CLI output will omit `managedByTenants`.

Also, for condition 1, the absence of `managedByTenants` from ARM's [Subscriptions - List](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/rest/api/resources/subscriptions/list) REST API will propagate all the way to Azure CLI output, causing breaking change.

